10/03/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Justice Ministry has sent a request to Austrian authorities for the extradition of Bosnian army general Jovan Divjak, media reported on Wednesday (March 9th).
Divjak was released on Tuesday after posting a 500,000-euro bail, but can't leave the country until the court decides on his case.
He was detained on March 3rd at the Vienna airport based on a warrant issued by Serbia.
He is wanted in connection with a May 1992 attack in Sarajevo against a Yugoslav National Army convoy, which left more than 40 soldiers dead.
(Srna, RTRS - 09/03/11)
